    "id": "qa-apr-vs-rate-1",
    "source_id": "1646",
    "question": "What is the difference between APR and interest rate?",
    "answer": "Interest rate is the cost of borrowing principal, while APR includes interest plus certain loan-related costs to show a broader borrowing cost. Comparing both helps you evaluate offers more accurately. You can learn more here: https://veecasa.com/apr-vs-rate/",
    "recommended_link": "https://veecasa.com/apr-vs-rate/",
